# PDF & Office Documents

How to produce PDF/DOCX/XLSX/PPTX deliverables without breaking the container.

## PDF — `mc pdf` (always, instead of local Chromium)

**DO NOT** install `puppeteer`/`chromium`/`playwright` locally — the agent
container is an x86 image under Rosetta on ARM; local Chrome binaries fail
with `rosetta error: failed to open elf`. The central mc-playwright sidecar
has Chromium ARM-native and renders via `page.pdf()`.

```bash
# RECOMMENDED: stdin — no path issues, always works
cat /tmp/report.md | mc pdf --title "Q1 Research Report" --file -

# Heredoc directly, no file needed
mc pdf --title "Zurich Weather" --file - << 'EOF'
# Weather Report
...
EOF

# Absolute path also works
mc pdf --title "Q1 Research Report" --file /tmp/report.md \
       --filename-prefix "medewo-brand-dna" \
       --description "Brand guidelines summarized from research"
```

Response: `{"ok": true, "deliverable_id": "<uuid>", "path": "...", "bytes": 15000}`.
Reuse `deliverable_id` directly for `mc telegram --file <deliverable_id>`.

### Forbidden alternatives (ARM/Rosetta conflict)

- `npm install puppeteer` + `page.pdf()` → x86 Chrome download, Rosetta failure
- `apt-get install chromium` → no root, fails
- `pip install playwright && playwright install chromium` → same x86/ARM issue

Only working alternative: Python `reportlab` for text-only PDFs. `mc pdf` is
always cleaner (consistently styled, no pip install in the container).

## Word / Excel / PowerPoint — direct via Python libraries

For DOCX / XLSX / PPTX, use the pre-installed libraries directly — there is
**no dedicated `mc` primitive for these formats**, they're ARM-neutral and
need no sidecar.

- `python-docx` for Word (.docx)
- `openpyxl` for Excel (.xlsx)
- `python-pptx` for PowerPoint (.pptx)
- `pandoc` (binary) for format conversions, e.g. Markdown → DOCX

```python
from docx import Document
doc = Document()
doc.add_heading("Q1 Report", 0)
doc.add_paragraph("...")
doc.save(f"/deliverables/{TASK_ID}/report.docx")
```

```bash
mc deliverable --title "Q1 Report" --type file --path /deliverables/$TASK_ID/report.docx
mc telegram "Q1 Report attached" --file <uuid>
```

Pandoc fallback: `pandoc report.md -o /deliverables/$TASK_ID/report.docx`

## Path disambiguation (applies to ALL formats)

| Path | Registerable as deliverable? |
|------|---|
| `/deliverables/<task_id>/` | Yes — directly |
| `/shared-deliverables/<task_id>/` (mc pdf, screenshots) | Yes — directly |
| `~/deliverables/`, `/home/agent/deliverables/` | No — not readable by the backend |
| `~/FreeCode/...`, `/workspace/...` | No — not readable by the backend |

A file created outside the two registerable prefixes MUST be copied there
before you register it as a deliverable.
